bug.short_desc: Software failed to display appstream compliant metainfo
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1212632 resulted search of molot in software
Description of problem: The issue occurred with the affected packages astigmatic-grand-hotel-fonts and typetype-molot-fonts containing metainfo. appstream-lib correctly validated the metainfo xml but Gnome Software failed to display those fonts. The metainfo in question followed upstream guideline.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 3.20.5
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Search either Grand Hotel or Molot in Software 2. 3.
Actual results: Neither fonts are listed
Expected results: Both fonts should be listed
Additional info: https://apps.fedoraproject.org/packages/typetype-molot-fonts/contents/#
https://apps.fedoraproject.org/packages/astigmatic-grand-hotel-fonts/contents/

So, these look like they build correctly:
https://github.com/hughsie/createrepo_as_logs/blob/master/t/typetype-molot-fonts.log https://github.com/hughsie/createrepo_as_logs/blob/master/a/astigmatic-grand-hotel-fonts.log
Can you try the appstream-data in updates-testing for f24 and tell me if it includes the fonts? Is so, please give positive karma.

Created attachment 1212933 Fixed research on Software after appstream-data update
Here is the screenshot showing the recent appstream-data update fixes the issue. I am giving karma on bodhi.
Closing this report because the current updated version solved the issue. See https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-1ff164044c
